ield? "" I hope we don't run into each other. " The man subconsciously glanced at the entrance of the cabin and turned his head to look ahead. Rhode opened his eyes. What happened? He stared blankly at the ceiling in front of him and his mind was in a daze. He remembered that he should have led his team to fight against the strongest boss in the Dragon Soul Continent, the Void Dragon, and successfully obtained the First Clear. He confirmed that he had obtained an achievement and a system notification.Then, the Void Dragon's final attack took his life. According to the original plan, Rhode should have resurrected in the graveyard and logged out. However, the moment he was killed by the Void Dragon, the entire world turned pitch-black as if it was forcibly isolated. Then, Rhode lost consciousness. How was this possible? Could it be that there was something wrong with the game? Rhode reluctantly turned his head and could see the blue sky and white clouds outside." Where am I? What is this place? What exactly happened? Is he still dreaming? Or am I still in the game? At least Rhode was sure that this place wasn't his small rental apartment. " Rhode frowned and tried to sit up. " Woo!!! " At this moment, a huge pain suddenly came from his chest. He gritted his teeth and stopped. Rhode realized that his left shoulder and chest were completely wrapped in bandages. Although he didn't know what happened, he could tell from the bloodstains that were seeping out from the bandages." This isn't a game! " Rhode was sure of this. Although technology was already advanced and the Dragon Soul Continent, the world's first virtual global online game, used a lot of high-tech technology, according to the rules, players couldn't feel pain. This was to differentiate reality from the game. At the same time, it also lowered the threshold for players.The game would use a series of methods to interfere with the normal game to warn and remind players, such as slowing down the player's movement 